##More than 20 countries under state of emergency, how China can help fight the epidemic?

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

We will use China's experience in epidemic prevention and control to help other countries affected by the epidemic tide over difficulties, and at the same time strengthen future cooperation opportunities. At this point, helping other countries is actually helping China itself

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Since the new government of Pakistan came into power, the development prospect of china-pakistan Economic Corridor began to be in a more uncertain state. Figure / IC

By Li Tie

Editor's Note: On March 15, a video went viral on the Internet showing Italians singing the Chinese national anthem and chanting "thank you, China" to show their gratitude to the Chinese people who have provided them with assistance in fighting the epidemic.

The global anti-epidemic process has entered a new stage.

Since the global anti-epidemic has entered a critical period, China has not only consolidated its own anti-epidemic achievements, but also timely sent assistance to the world and provided experience. COVID-19 is a brand new unknown virus, China in the first time to identify the pathogen, to share relevant information to the world, so that the international community can be timely understanding and prevention of the virus. In the face of the epidemic, China has quickly taken effective measures to strengthen detection and isolation, seal off cities, establish shelter hospitals and suspend classes for students. The World Health Organization says China's epidemic prevention experience shows that new cases of pneumonia can be contained.

In addition, China has extended a helping hand to the countries and regions affected by the outbreak. On the evening of March 12, an anti-epidemic medical expert group jointly organized by the Chinese Health and Health Commission and the Red Cross Society arrived in the Italian capital, Rome, with medical supplies donated by the Chinese side. Italy was one of the first countries in Europe to declare a state of emergency in response to the outbreak of new coronary pneumonia. According to a French 24-hour television report, after a confirmed case of new coronary pneumonia emerged in the capital, Rome, the Italian government declared a six-month state of emergency as early as January 31. Italy's local governments will have more power in a state of emergency and will be able to skip some of the red tape in implementing an outbreak response.

According to china.com.cn, doctors at the Institute of Medical Science in Italy said after a meeting with a Chinese expert group that, chinese doctors "share in every aspect from prevention, diagnosis to treatment, which is very valuable and effective. It has brought Italy the most advanced and first-hand experience in fighting the epidemic. ". "We are in great need of the Chinese experience and have put forward plans for further cooperation in scientific research, " said Nicholas of Cusa, director of the clinic and Medical Research Department at the hospital

In addition to Italy, China has also sent expert teams to Iran, Iraq and other countries, and provided anti-epidemic material assistance to South Korea, Japan and many countries in Europe, these include face masks, protective clothing, goggles and a new cap nucleic acid test kit.

China has set up a joint prevention and control cooperation mechanism with South Korea and a joint expert group with the European Union. Chinese experts also held video conferences with the European Union, the African Union and ASEAN as well as a number of countries for experience sharing and technical exchanges. China has released several versions of the diagnosis, treatment and prevention of new coronary pneumonia, which have also been translated and shared in various languages.

With the global economy reeling from the outbreak, China, on the one hand, is trying to prevent the re-spread of the epidemic caused by imported cases; on the other hand, it is also actively taking international cooperation to help the stricken countries tide over the difficulties, and strengthen future opportunities for cooperation. Li Tie, chief economist at the China Urban and small town development center, recently wrote in Caijing that helping other countries at this time is also helping China itself. At this time, we should not play up the institutional problems of other countries' epidemic prevention measures. China should take this opportunity to continue to promote the process of globalization, implement the "Belt and Road" International Cooperation Mechanism and play an important role in it. (following is the main text)

There is serious uncertainty about the current worldwide trend of the epidemic of NCP. But in China, because takes the decisive measure promptly, has obtained the obvious result. Although the risk has not yet been lifted, the trend towards containment of the epidemic is clear. At present, the focus of prevention and control has begun to prevent the spread of domestic origin to all places, to focus on the prevention of foreign imports.

In fact, we are concerned about the evolution of the epidemic in the international arena. We should focus on two aspects. First, how to prevent the re-spread of the epidemic caused by imports from abroad; and second, what kind of international cooperation should be adopted to help the affected countries tide over the difficulties, and strengthen future opportunities for cooperation. At this point, helping others is also helping China itself. At this time, we should not play up the institutional problems of other countries' epidemic prevention measures, neglecting to take advantage of this opportunity, which may help China continue to push forward the process of globalization and implement the "Belt and Road" International Cooperation Mechanism, to play an important role in our lives.

The situation has reversed, and a new judgment is needed

In the early stages of the outbreak, many were pessimistic that China might once again face blockades in some countries, that the economic risks would shift from domestic shutdowns to international blockades, and that some industrial chains might be forced to shift outward. According to the performance of some countries at that time and the analysis of scholars, it seems that this possibility exists.

But what many people didn't expect was that things had turned around. Many countries that have proposed closing their borders to China are also being forced to do so, presumably for much longer than China has gone through. Because China, although the outbreak of large-scale epidemic relatively early, but in the shortest possible time to solve the problem. For other countries, the inability to take decisive action for a variety of reasons may even magnify the spread of the epidemic.

In this case, judge again the global industrial chain in space will cause what kind of changes, and how to take advantage of the post-epidemic period how to play the "Belt and Road" cooperation mechanism, what kind of strategic measures should be taken is particularly important.

From the point of view of international trade, from temporarily closing the door to China because of the epidemic, to now China may have to close the door because of the epidemic in other countries, in fact, it has a huge impact on the global industrial chain and international trade. Whether China can continue to maintain the current pattern of international trade without closing its doors may require careful judgment and decision-making. I believe that there should be no one-size-fits-all closure policy for people and goods from outside China, but inspection measures should be strengthened, although they will cost a certain amount of manpower and capital, but it is important for both sides to maintain long-term cooperative relations as well as existing economic interests.

From an investment perspective, though, some industries have shifted to the rest of Asia as China's labor and land costs have risen. But through this epidemic control effect, China's institutional advantage is that it can experience any major disaster and sudden crisis, and will not lead to out of control of National Governance. It is particularly important to build investor confidence. Many people believe that long-term investment in China mainly depends on cost advantage, in fact, the stability of the system advantage and the formation of the entire industrial chain and national quality, investors must also consider factors.

At the moment of crisis when the epidemic is spreading around the world, another important factor that will test China is how to take advantage of the favorable opportunity to increase its efforts to attract foreign investment, which is also a very important policy focus at present. For example, the announcement of new preferential policies for foreign investment, especially in the light of the new characteristics of the epidemic, will determine what kind of protection measures and quarantine measures should be provided for foreign investors. The moment of truth may be used to wipe out the gloom of recent years and create a new situation for China's international trade and investment.

Using China's experience to help fight the global epidemic

From the pattern of production capacity distribution, although we see the decline in oil prices and other factors, to increase China's oil and gas reserves, reduce corporate costs brought good. However, the production of a large number of emergency medical materials which are supposed to be used to deal with the sudden epidemic has the possibility of surplus in the post-epidemic era. If China takes advantage of the outbreak to put its surplus medical assets into a cooperative mechanism in time to support friendly countries with "Belt and Road" cooperation, it will solve the problem of overcapacity, it's also a great help to these countries. Of course, it also foreshadows mutual trust among countries, enterprises and people.

In view of the development trend of Internet and information technology, China's experience in dealing with epidemic situation has many scientific and intelligent factors, which are derived from the popularization of Internet application and the wide application of various urban smart technologies in the market. While promoting the "Belt and Road" cooperation mechanism, we can also promote the use of the Internet and information technology in cities, including for the city and community residents during the closure and self-isolation of psychological support and life support, as well as in the resumption of work to take advantage of the Internet, the use of video conferencing and Internet office mode, and so on, in particular, the promotion of a variety of back-office soft technology and front-office hard technology.

In short, these Chinese advantages, which have proved effective in China's fight against the epidemic, can be taken as a key element in supporting the "Belt and Road" countries through the construction of the epidemic prevention system. This needs to be done when an expert support team is established, full consideration will be given to the mix of members and technical staff in this area.

The reason why we propose to establish a global epidemic prevention system through a "Belt and Road" cooperation mechanism is that it can be quickly responded to through the existing mechanism, and that the countries participating in this mechanism are basically friendly countries with China; Third, it can also expand the influence of "Belt and Road" through this mechanism. Fourth, in this special period, people rely on the traditional mechanism, can increase the mechanism of mutual trust through epidemic prevention; Fifth, through the "Belt and Road" financial cooperation mechanism, to help the affected countries to solve the problem of financial pressure.

For countries that oppose the "Belt and Road" or even the "dismantling of the Taiwan Straits, " we can still take a grass-roots, post-national approach and let them know the benefits of enjoying the "Belt and Road" mechanism of international cooperation. China's goal is to expand the scope of cooperation between the countries concerned, to resolve contradictions and antagonism, to distinguish between friendly countries and competing countries, and to adopt various ways to turn enemies into friends to the greatest extent possible. Of course, we should also adhere to the basic principles of international exchanges, and adopt different policies and measures to distinguish countries and peoples from those countries that continue to maintain their obstinate positions.

In recent years, the pattern of globalization has encountered a severe challenge from unilateralism. But judging from the trend of development, unilateralism is not popular. The global outbreak of this epidemic, along with the level of development of each country, governance capacity and emergency response measures, is a serious challenge. Although China has been successful in dealing with the epidemic at home, it is bound to be unable to cope with the global epidemic situation alone. Therefore, how to make good use of the challenges and opportunities brought by the crisis, to achieve the reshaping of the global pattern of trade and breakthrough, it is now or never. Specific recommendations are as follows:

Establishment of a "Belt and Road" National Cooperation Mechanism for epidemic prevention and control. Where it is not convenient for people to come and go, consensus can be reached through video exchanges and cooperation can be achieved through mechanisms.

The establishment of a "Belt and Road" National Assistance Fund for the prevention of new crown disease can raise funds from relevant banks, the Ministry of Finance and other aspects, but also invited "Belt and Road" countries to participate in the Fund's investment.

We will strengthen the construction of the "Belt and Road" National Public Health and epidemic prevention system, and strengthen the functions of the relevant Chinese departments and the Public Health and epidemic prevention system in this regard. Epidemic Prevention Assistance and support to relevant countries should be accomplished through system building.

Under the "Belt and Road" cooperation mechanism, the exchange of experience in epidemic prevention and control, including medical and urban governance, as well as the application of Internet information technology and experience. Assistance can be provided through human and technical support.

The writer is chief economist at the Center for Urban and small town reform and development in China
